this function is helpful is when creating an API"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"that allows the user to provide a callback function that returns a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":".  We certainly want to allow the user the flexibility to"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"return a non-floating reference from this callback (for the case"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"where the value that is being returned already exists).","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"At the same time, the style of the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" API makes it likely that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"for newly-created ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant","isActive":true},{"text":" instances, the user can be saved some","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"typing if they are allowed to return a "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" with a floating"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"reference."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Using this function on the return value of the user’s callback allows"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the user to do whichever is more convenient for them.  The caller"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"will always receives exactly one full reference to the value: either","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the one that was returned in the first place, or a floating reference","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"that has been converted to a full reference."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This function has an odd interaction when combined with"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_variant_ref_sink()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" running at the same time in another thread on"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the same "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" instance.  If "},{"code":"g_variant_ref_sink()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" runs first then"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the result will be that the floating reference is converted to a hard"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"reference.  If "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_variant_take_ref()"},{"text":" runs first then the result will","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"be that the floating reference is converted to a hard reference and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"an additional reference on top of that one is added.  It is best to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"avoid this situation.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/VariantRef","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/VariantRef\/VariantProtocol-Implementations"]]},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/VariantRef":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"VariantRef"}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/VariantRef","type":"topic","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"VariantRef"}],"title":"VariantRef","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/variantref","abstract":[{"code":"GVariant","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is a variant datatype; it can contain one or more values"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"along with 